250 g Ground Beef
4 g Pumpkin Pie Spice Mix
2 unit Sandwich Bun
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
2 unit Garlic, cloves
4 tbsp Ketchup
300 g Yellow Potato
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
100 g Bacon Strips
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 tbsp Butter*
1 tsp Salt*
½ tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425°F.
Lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium (approx. 400°F).
Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/4-inch rounds.
To an unlined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with half the Zesty Garlic Blend, salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 25-28 min, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden.

Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
To a medium bowl, add ground beef, panko, Pumpkin Pie Spice Mix, half the garlic, half the grainy mustard, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) salt and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) pepper. Mix to combine.
Divide mixture into 2 (4) 7-inch sausage shapes and flatten sligthly. Set aside.

Meanwhile, on a parchment-lined baking sheet, arrange bacon in a single layer.
Roast in the bottom of the oven for 10-14 min, until bacon is crisp and cooked through.** Transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to cool.

To a small bowl, add mayo, remaining grainy mustard and remaining garlic. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
To a small microwave-safe bowl, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter and microwave for 30 sec, until soft. Add remaining Zesty Garlic Blend, stir to combine.
Spread butter on tops and bottoms of sandwich buns.

Brush sausages with 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. Season with salt.
Add sausage to the grill. Close lid and grill sausage for 5-7 min, flipping once, until cooked through.**
Place buns buttered-side down on one side of the grill. Close lid and grill over medium heat for 1 min, then flip buns and cook for 1-2 min, until warm.

If desired, warm bacon in the oven for 1 min.
Spread half the ketchup on the bottom buns.
Top bottom buns with bacon, sausage and remaining ketchup. Close with top buns.
Divide potato coins between plates.
Serve mustard-mayo dipper on the side.